#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Validation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Verify gitignore is working correctly:
#
#   # Check if a file would be ignored
#   git check-ignore -v [filename]
#
#   # List all ignored files
#   git status --ignored
#
#   # Debug why a file is/isn't ignored
#   git check-ignore -v --no-index [filename]
#
# Common Issues:
#
#   "File still tracked" - Already committed files need: git rm --cached [file]
#   "Pattern not working" - Check for typos, trailing spaces
#   "Too many files ignored" - Pattern may be too broad, use ! to negate
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Modification Policy
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Safe to Modify:
#   ✅ Add new patterns for project-specific files
#   ✅ Add comments explaining patterns
#   ✅ Use ! to include specific files from ignored directories
#
# Modify with Care:
#   ⚠️ Removing patterns (may expose sensitive files)
#   ⚠️ Broad patterns like * or **/* (may exclude needed files)
#   ⚠️ Patterns affecting shared IDE configs
#
# NEVER Modify:
#   ❌ Remove .env and secrets patterns without team discussion
#   ❌ 4-block documentation structure
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Closing Note
